	<div class="commentBody">
		<div id="comment_body_65308045"><p>I have VLC as my primary media player. Every time the phone is restarted, it blanks its own cache about what music I have on it, and refuses to play anything until it's searched my storage for music which usually takes half an hour and only starts when you start the app (it doesn't, say, run in the background doing this automatically on boot.) It's f---ing annoying as it is, but at least it only happens once every few weeks.</p><p>I'm sure this is an edge case, I mean, with the headphone jack removal being passive<span class="substr"> </span></p></div>
